TitleEnglish: A Record of a Mortal’s Journey to Immortality
SummaryEnglish: A poor and ordinary boy from a village joins a minor sect in Jiang Hu and becomes an Unofficial Disciple by chance. How will Han Li, a commoner by birth, establish a foothold for himself in in his sect? With his mediocre aptitude, he must successfully traverse the treacherous path of cultivation and avoid the notice of those who may do him harm. This is a story of an ordinary mortal who, against all odds, clashes with devilish demons and ancient celestials in order to find his own path towards immortality.

6.SummaryEnglish: With the help of the little green bottle, Han Li made pills and practiced on the island, his power recovered to the foundation building stage, and he trained Qu Hun into an [outside body incarnation]. In the south of the sky, the mortal [Mo Cai Huan] died. Many years later, Han Li came out of seclusion and met two beautiful women [Yan Li] and [Yuan Yao].

7.SummaryEnglish: Han Li wanted to buy some materials and met Wen Qiang again. Hearing that if he participated in the Demon Suppression Ceremony and won the championship, he could get the Dust-Reducing Pill, which could lower the threshold for forming a pill, so he decided to give it a try. Also attending the Demon Suppression Ceremony were the head of the Miaoyin Sect who was in the Jindan stage and his daughter Wang Ning. Han Li and Wang Ning passed by each other and felt an inexplicable familiarity.
